cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is about self-supervised learning of optical flow, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of a CNN for better flow estimation, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses a self-supervised approach, which involves designing an algorithm to learn from data without explicit supervision, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The use of temporal information from multiple frames also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
